



give me .gitegnore file

Here’s a solid .gitignore you can use for most projects (Node.js + Python + general dev). It covers common cases:

# -----------------------
# OS files
# -----------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# -----------------------
# Logs
# -----------------------
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*

# -----------------------
# Environment variables
# -----------------------
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# -----------------------
# Node.js
# -----------------------
node_modules/
dist/
build/
.cache/
.next/
out/
coverage/

# -----------------------
# Python
# -----------------------
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo
*.pyd
*.sqlite3
*.db
*.log

# Virtual environments
venv/
env/
ENV/

# -----------------------
# IDE / Editor
# -----------------------
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
*.swo

# -----------------------
# Dependency directories
# -----------------------
bower_components/
jspm_packages/

# -----------------------
# Package managers
# -----------------------
package-lock.json
yarn.lock
pnpm-lock.yaml

# -----------------------
# Testing
# -----------------------
coverage/
.nyc_output/

# -----------------------
# Build output
# -----------------------
dist/
build/
*.tgz

# -----------------------
# Docker
# -----------------------
docker-compose.override.yml

# -----------------------
# Misc
# -----------------------
*.pem
*.key
*.crt
🔧 Notes (important)
If you're working with Node.js, you may want to keep package-lock.json → remove it from ignore.

If you're working with Python, keep requirements.txt (don’t ignore it).

.env is ignored to protect secrets.

If you want, I can give you a project-specific .gitignore (React / Django / Node API / React Native) tailored exactly to your setup.



.env
